# Project domain

## Expense

A single credit card transaction.

| Field | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| Date | Transaction date |
| Merchant | Merchant reference |
| Full amount | Original value on the statement |
| Share | User’s portion (default 100%) |
| Personal amount | `full amount × share` — **used in all analytics** |
| Tag ids | List of tag ids |
| Collection id | Optional; omit = routine |

Other fields (original value, currency, notes, etc.) stay as implemented.

- Amounts may be **negative** (refunds); they reduce totals in analytics. UI: visually distinct (e.g. green + refund indicator).
- **At most one collection.** No collection ⇒ **routine**.
- Creating from a merchant with a **default share**: apply share silently; compute personal amount; **full amount is always preserved**.
- UI when share is below 100%: show both full and personal (e.g. `₪300 · your share ₪100`).

## Tag

- **Unique name**; `tags` table is the single source of truth (fast lookup, quick-select).
- **Flat** — no hierarchy.
- Expense can have any number of tags.
- Add-by-name: **reuse existing id** if name exists; no duplicate rows.

## Merchant

Business or payee.

- **Canonical name** — raw statement string (e.g. `AMZN MKTP US*1234`); **unique**.
- **Alias** — user-facing name (e.g. `Amazon`).
- **Tag ids** — default tags for this merchant (**read-time** on expenses).
- **Optional default share** — new expenses from this merchant inherit share and personal amount; **does not retroactively change existing expenses**.

**Read API:** expense responses expose two lists (do not merge on the server):

1. **Expense tags** — on the expense row  
2. **Merchant tags** — from the expense’s merchant at read time  

Client merges and dedupes for display. A tag may appear in both lists. Merchant tag changes apply immediately for all expenses from that merchant (read-time).

## Collection

Named group for one bounded event or project (e.g. `USA trip 2025`, `kitchen renovation`). **Unique name**; optional date range.

- Expense **at most one** collection.
- Collection expenses are **isolated from routine analytics** (excluded from monthly routine breakdown).
- Answers: cost of that event and its breakdown.

## Routine

Not a stored entity. **All expenses with no collection** — day-to-day spend. **Routine analytics** (e.g. monthly breakdown by tag) use **only** this subset.
